Monks, two dhamma-teachings of the wayfarer arahant. a rightly awakened one.
take place one after the other. What two? ‘Look at evil as evil’ is the first
dhamma-teaching.  ‘Seeing evil as evil, be disgusted therewith, be cleansed
of it, be freed of it’ is the second dhamma-teaching. These two
dhamma-teachings of the wayfarer take place one after the other.
